<p>Well no it cant. The US military is only capable of &#8216;defeating&#8217; weak and poorly armed opponents, and most time it cant even do that very well. The other thing he fails to take into account, a general economic crisis in the US, will also be the end of the US military as a global garrison force. Just like the Soviet collapse meant tanks and ships rusting away in fields and ports, and planes grounded for lack of fuel and spare parts, so it will be for the amerikans. </p>
<p>What he should have high-lighted is the real threat the US poses. That it will decide to lash out at the world *before* a general collapse, mostly out of sheer spite, while it still has the means to do so. If it waits till the collapse is in full swing, what (useless) military power it still possesses will be useless in any event. Its strange the author seems to think US military &#8216;power&#8217; will somehow remain intact enough to engage in &#8216;defeating&#8217; (who?!) through the crises he sees coming.</p>
