<p>The caveat to this, is that as we approach the limits, the risk become systemic as we saw in 2008 but the people in charge understand that perfectly and will be ready to throw anything at the problem, including the kitchen sink, the next time a crisis occur. So it cannot be a liquidity crisis, not this time. But black swans can come from many directions. Their only common characteristic is to be unpredicted. And once again they will be, have little doubts about it!</p>
